    options: [
        'A. 1 only ',
        'B. 2 only ',
        'C. Both 1 and 2 ',
        'D. Neither 1 nor 2 ',
    ],
    answer: `Answer: A`,
    exp: `Explanation:  The Modern Periodic Law states: 'Properties of elements are a periodic function of their atomic number'.  The atomic number gives us the number of protons in the nucleus of an atom and this number increases by one in going from one element to the next.  Elements, when arranged in order of increasing atomic number Z, lead us to the classification known as the Modern Periodic Table.  Prediction of properties of elements could be made with more precision when elements were arranged on the basis of increasing atomic number.  The Modern Periodic Table has 18 vertical columns known as ‘groups’ and 7 horizontal rows known as ‘periods’. `
